==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trypsin
<hw>Tryp"sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a rubbing,
fr. <?/ to rub, grind. So called because it causes protein to break up
or to fall apart.]</ety> <fld>(physiol.)</fld> <def>A proteolytic enzyme
present in the pancreatic juice. Unlike the pepsin of the gastric juice,
it acts in a neutral or alkaline fluid, and not only converts the
albuminous matter of the food into soluble peptones, but also, in part,
into leucin and tyrosin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trypsinogen</ent>⟦br⟧
